Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
verifyEndCap(25.10)                                        verifyEndCap(25.10)

Name
       verifyEndCap  -  Checks  whether  pre/post cap cells have been inserted
       correctly based on setEndCapMode settings

Syntax
       verifyEndCap

       [-help]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-coreBoundaryOnly]

       [-error <integer>]

       [-ignore_macro <SCLA,...>]

       [-powerDomain <string>]

       [-report <filename>]

       [-row <string>]

       [-tripleWell]

       [-wrongLocation]

       Checks whether pre/post cap cells have been inserted correctly based on
       setEndCapMode settings. Use this command  after  running  addEndCap  to
       flag violations such as:

              * Inserted end cap cell is of wrong type

              * End cap cell is missing

       If  you use verifyEndCap with the -wrongLocation option, it also checks
       whether the end cap cells are inserted in the right location.  Use  the
       -powerDomain  option  to  check  end  cap cells inserted for a specific
       power domain.

       Additionally, you can use verifyEndCap -tripleWell to check triple well
       insertion. Triple well technology is used to isolate p-well  from  sub-
       strate using a deep n-well.

       You  can view the violation markers generated by verifyEndCap in Viola-
       tion Browser.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each verifyEndCap parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man verifyEndCap

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the area in which endcaps are to be verified.

       -coreBoundaryOnly
              Checks endcaps only at the core-boundary and  not  abutting  ob-
              structions.

              Note:  The -coreBoundaryOnly option does not support triple well
              cap insertion.

       -error integer
              Specifies the maximum number of errors to report.

       -ignore_macro <SCLA,...>
              Specifies the macro to be ignored.

       -powerDomain string
              Specifies the power domain to be checked.  Use  this  option  to
              check end cap cells inserted for the specified power domain.

       -report filename
              Specifies the file name for the verifyEndCap report.

       -row string
              Specifies the row to check.

       -tripleWell
              Checks  triple well insertion. Only checks the cell lists speci-
              fied in setEndCapMode.

       -wrongLocation
              Checks for cap cells that are not inserted in  the  right  loca-
              tion. If you specify this option, verifyEndCap marks with a vio-
              lation  marker  any cap cell that is not on the beginning/end of
              the row or not on the boundary of the design/ block design.

Examples
              * The following set of commands verifies whether cap cell inser-
                tion is as per the setEndCapMode settings and generates a  de-
                fault report file in the active folder:

                setEndCapMode -leftEdge EC_LE10 -rightEdge EC_RE10

                verifyEndCap

              * The following command verifies end cap insertion and generates
                a report named endcap.rpt:

                setEndCapMode -leftEdge EC_LE10 -rightEdge EC_RE10

                verifyEndCap -report endcap.rpt

              * The  following command verifies triple well insertion. It also
                checks the cap cells that are not inserted in the right  loca-
                tion and reports up to 10000 errors:

                setEndCapMode -leftEdge EC_LE10 -rightEdge EC_RE10 -bottomEdge
                EC_BE10 \

                              -leftBottomCorner     EC_LBC10    -leftTopCorner
                EC_LTC10 \

                              -rightBottomCorner   EC_RBC10    -rightTopCorner
                EC_RTC10 \

                              -topEdge EC_TE10

                verifyEndCap -tripleWell -wrongLocation -error 10000

Related Information
              * "Verifying  End Cap Violations" in the Identifying and Viewing
                Violations chapter of User Guide.

              * "Adding End-Cap Cells" in the Placing the  Design  chapter  of
                User Guide.

